-- Berkshire Hathaway's Class A shares cross $200,000
-- 
-- Thu Aug 14, 2014 10:25AM EDT
-- None



Aug 14 (Reuters) - Berkshire Hathaway Inc's <BRKa.N> class A shares <BRKa.N> crossed $200,000 for the first time on Thursday.

Class A shares of Berkshire, which have never been split, rose as high as $200,279.99. The Class B shares, which are more widely held and were split when the company purchased Burlington Northern Santa Fe, were lately up 0.3 percent to $133.52 a share.